\f1\b\fs32 \cf2 Al Ewing
\f0\b0\fs20 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\sa200\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 Al Ewing was raised in the Antelope Valley and after a variety of careers, including serving 8 years in the Air Force, he arrived at Hart Park in 2007.\'a0 Before long, Al was busy working on a wide variety of events at the Park which brought his creativity and artistic and musical abilities into play.\'a0 Whether it was an art show, a quilting exhibit, a movie night or an afternoon concert in the Park, Al attacked them all with enthusiasm and the energy to make the events successful.\'a0 When the Friends of Hart Park sponsored an event, Al was always there to help in whatever way his talents might be best used.\'a0 Operating the sound system, acting as the DJ, putting out tables, or setting up a pop-up sun shade all fell within Al\'92s job description along with a myriad of other activities.\'a0 Al and his new bride, Linda, will soon be motoring off to Georgia to take possession of their 9 acre estate, and they have already begun to make plans for the types of activities which will occupy their time.\'a0 It is with deep appreciation that we wish Al and Linda the very best as they approach their new life in the South, and we will look forward to hearing from them and learning of their adventures in a future newsletter.\'a0 Have a life of happiness and please remember your many friends at Hart Park, as we will certainly remember you!
